        <h3><a id="Q3">How is vCruit different from putting videos on my website?</a></h3>
        <p>
          If you answer "Yes" to all the below questions you might consider using your website instead of vCruit. Ohterwise, vCruit will be a far better option.
        </p>
        <p>+ Do you know who maintains your company's website? Would they add a video page for you?</p>
        <p>+ If you have access to your website, do you have the knowledge to add a web page and a video?</p>
        <p>+ Do you know how long it takes to setup a custom landing page for five different videos and generate linked images to them?</p>
        <p>+ Do you want to spend your valuable time creating and maintaining numerous landing pages?</p>
        <p><strong>Conclusion: If you have multiple videos or multiple people uploading videos, using your website will become very tedious.</strong></p>
