        <h3><a id="Q4">How is vCruit different from putting my videos directly on LinkedIn, Facebook, or Twitter?</a></h3>
        <p><strong>Reason 1: LinkedIn and Twitter are distribution channels and do not host videos.</strong> You can post videos on them, but you need somewhere else to host your video.</p>
        <p><strong>Reason 2: They are public social media channels and limit your distribution channels.</strong> What if you want to send your video via email? What if there is a video that you want to send to a smaller group or only one specific person?</p>
        <p><strong>Reason 3: They lack custom call to action buttons and granular analytics.</strong> This will make it harder to convert a passive viewer into an active relationship.</p>
        <p><strong>Conclusion: LinkedIn, Facebook, and Twitter are great distribution channels, but you need a platform that will host your videos, allow distribution through multiple channels, and maximize viewer conversion.</strong></p>
